{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Good morning. How are you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":4702,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5936,"text":"It's been great, hasn't it?"},{"time":8273,"text":"I've been blown away by the whole thing."},{"time":10753,"text":"In fact, I'm leaving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12269,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18015,"text":"There have been three themes\nrunning through the conference"},{"time":21246,"text":"which are relevant\nto what I want to talk about."},{"time":23777,"text":"One is the extraordinary\nevidence of human creativity"},{"time":28491,"text":"in all of the presentations that we've had"},{"time":30928,"text":"and in all of the people here."},{"time":32753,"text":"Just the variety of it\nand the range of it."},{"time":36158,"text":"The second is\nthat it's put us in a place"},{"time":38325,"text":"where we have no idea\nwhat's going to happen,"},{"time":40846,"text":"in terms of the future."},{"time":42261,"text":"No idea how this may play out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"I have an interest in education."},{"time":46916,"text":"Actually, what I find is everybody\nhas an interest in education."},{"time":51072,"text":"Don't you?"},{"time":52234,"text":"I find this very interesting."},{"time":53739,"text":"If you're at a dinner party,"},{"time":55596,"text":"and you say you work in education --"},{"time":57882,"text":"Actually, you're not often\nat dinner parties, frankly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60870,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":64690,"text":"If you work in education,\nyou're not asked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67142,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70257,"text":"And you're never asked back, curiously.\nThat's strange to me."},{"time":74000,"text":"But if you are, and you say to somebody,"},{"time":76499,"text":"you know, they say, \"What do you do?\""},{"time":78300,"text":"and you say you work in education,"},{"time":80000,"text":"you can see the blood run from their face."},{"time":82100,"text":"They're like, \"Oh my God,\"\nyou know, \"Why me?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":84404,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86065,"text":"\"My one night out all week.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":87712,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90346,"text":"But if you ask about their education,\nthey pin you to the wall."},{"time":93611,"text":"Because it's one of those things\nthat goes deep with people, am I right?"},{"time":97194,"text":"Like religion, and money and other things."},{"time":100559,"text":"So I have a big interest in education,\nand I think we all do."},{"time":104935,"text":"We have a huge vested interest in it,"},{"time":106851,"text":"partly because it's education\nthat's meant to take us into this future"},{"time":110195,"text":"that we can't grasp."},{"time":111873,"text":"If you think of it,\nchildren starting school this year"},{"time":115396,"text":"will be retiring in 2065."},{"time":120209,"text":"Nobody has a clue,"},{"time":121867,"text":"despite all the expertise that's been\non parade for the past four days,"},{"time":125450,"text":"what the world will look like\nin five years' time."},{"time":128000,"text":"And yet we're meant\nto be educating them for it."},{"time":130318,"text":"So the unpredictability,\nI think, is extraordinary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132892,"text":"And the third part of this"},{"time":134283,"text":"is that we've all agreed, nonetheless,"},{"time":136344,"text":"on the really extraordinary\ncapacities that children have --"},{"time":141673,"text":"their capacities for innovation."},{"time":144031,"text":"I mean, Sirena last night\nwas a marvel, wasn't she?"},{"time":146566,"text":"Just seeing what she could do."},{"time":148200,"text":"And she's exceptional, but I think\nshe's not, so to speak,"},{"time":153000,"text":"exceptional in the whole of childhood."},{"time":156980,"text":"What you have there is a person\nof extraordinary dedication"},{"time":159800,"text":"who found a talent."},{"time":161091,"text":"And my contention is,\nall kids have tremendous talents."},{"time":163800,"text":"And we squander them, pretty ruthlessly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165800,"text":"So I want to talk about education"},{"time":168000,"text":"and I want to talk about creativity."},{"time":169896,"text":"My contention is that creativity now\nis as important in education as literacy,"},{"time":175939,"text":"and we should treat it\nwith the same status."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178827,"text":"(Applause) Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180822,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":185485,"text":"That was it, by the way."},{"time":186768,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187795,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189934,"text":"So, 15 minutes left."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191635,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":194595,"text":"Well, I was born... no."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196511,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199567,"text":"I heard a great story recently\n-- I love telling it --"},{"time":202336,"text":"of a little girl\nwho was in a drawing lesson."},{"time":205075,"text":"She was six, and she was\nat the back, drawing,"},{"time":207234,"text":"and the teacher said this girl\nhardly ever paid attention,"},{"time":210058,"text":"and in this drawing lesson, she did."},{"time":211868,"text":"The teacher was fascinated."},{"time":213232,"text":"She went over to her,\nand she said, \"What are you drawing?\""},{"time":216018,"text":"And the girl said, \"I'm\ndrawing a picture of God.\""},{"time":219642,"text":"And the teacher said, \"But nobody\nknows what God looks like.\""},{"time":222984,"text":"And the girl said,\n\"They will, in a minute.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":225096,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":236662,"text":"When my son was four in England --"},{"time":239413,"text":"Actually, he was four\neverywhere, to be honest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241628,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243404,"text":"If we're being strict about it,\nwherever he went, he was four that year."},{"time":246815,"text":"He was in the Nativity play.\nDo you remember the story?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249477,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":250720,"text":"No, it was big, it was a big story."},{"time":252571,"text":"Mel Gibson did the sequel,\nyou may have seen it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254900,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256185,"text":"\"Nativity II.\""},{"time":257519,"text":"But James got the part of Joseph,\nwhich we were thrilled about."},{"time":261678,"text":"We considered this to be\none of the lead parts."},{"time":264239,"text":"We had the place crammed\nfull of agents in T-shirts:"},{"time":266740,"text":"\"James Robinson IS Joseph!\" (Laughter)"},{"time":269000,"text":"He didn't have to speak,"},{"time":270631,"text":"but you know the bit\nwhere the three kings come in?"},{"time":273093,"text":"They come in bearing gifts,\ngold, frankincense and myrrh."},{"time":275848,"text":"This really happened."},{"time":276986,"text":"We were sitting there and I think\nthey just went out of sequence,"},{"time":280100,"text":"because we talked to the little boy\nafterward and we said,"},{"time":282900,"text":"\"You OK with that?\" And he said,\n\"Yeah, why? Was that wrong?\""},{"time":285800,"text":"They just switched."},{"time":286900,"text":"The three boys came in,"},{"time":288100,"text":"four-year-olds with tea towels\non their heads,"},{"time":290311,"text":"and they put these boxes down,"},{"time":291826,"text":"and the first boy said,\n\"I bring you gold.\""},{"time":293899,"text":"And the second boy said,\n\"I bring you myrrh.\""},{"time":296061,"text":"And the third boy said, \"Frank sent this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":298089,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310711,"text":"What these things have in common\nis that kids will take a chance."},{"time":313825,"text":"If they don't know, they'll have a go."},{"time":316457,"text":"Am I right? They're not\nfrightened of being wrong."},{"time":320893,"text":"I don't mean to say that being wrong\nis the same thing as being creative."},{"time":324886,"text":"What we do know is,\nif you're not prepared to be wrong,"},{"time":328000,"text":"you'll never come up\nwith anything original --"},{"time":330391,"text":"if you're not prepared to be wrong."},{"time":332877,"text":"And by the time they get to be adults,\nmost kids have lost that capacity."},{"time":337406,"text":"They have become\nfrightened of being wrong."},{"time":339950,"text":"And we run our companies like this."},{"time":341664,"text":"We stigmatize mistakes."},{"time":343340,"text":"And we're now running\nnational education systems"},{"time":345666,"text":"where mistakes are the worst\nthing you can make."},{"time":348700,"text":"And the result is that\nwe are educating people"},{"time":351932,"text":"out of their creative capacities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354247,"text":"Picasso once said this, he said\nthat all children are born artists."},{"time":358749,"text":"The problem is to remain an artist\nas we grow up."},{"time":361995,"text":"I believe this passionately,\nthat we don't grow into creativity,"},{"time":365100,"text":"we grow out of it."},{"time":366980,"text":"Or rather, we get educated out of it."},{"time":369247,"text":"So why is this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370826,"text":"I lived in Stratford-on-Avon\nuntil about five years ago."},{"time":374931,"text":"In fact, we moved\nfrom Stratford to Los Angeles."},{"time":377872,"text":"So you can imagine\nwhat a seamless transition that was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"Actually, we lived in a place\ncalled Snitterfield,"},{"time":384400,"text":"just outside Stratford,"},{"time":385675,"text":"which is where\nShakespeare's father was born."},{"time":388082,"text":"Are you struck by a new thought? I was."},{"time":390481,"text":"You don't think of Shakespeare\nhaving a father, do you?"},{"time":393100,"text":"Do you? Because you don't think\nof Shakespeare being a child, do you?"},{"time":397000,"text":"Shakespeare being seven?"},{"time":398591,"text":"I never thought of it."},{"time":399864,"text":"I mean, he was seven at some point."},{"time":401572,"text":"He was in somebody's\nEnglish class, wasn't he?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":403906,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410717,"text":"How annoying would that be?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412070,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419729,"text":"\"Must try harder.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":420788,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424712,"text":"Being sent to bed by his dad, you know,\nto Shakespeare, \"Go to bed, now!"},{"time":428200,"text":"And put the pencil down.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":430652,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431750,"text":"\"And stop speaking like that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":433329,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":437244,"text":"\"It's confusing everybody.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":438592,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443739,"text":"Anyway, we moved\nfrom Stratford to Los Angeles,"},{"time":449101,"text":"and I just want to say a word\nabout the transition."},{"time":451566,"text":"My son didn't want to come."},{"time":453000,"text":"I've got two kids;\nhe's 21 now, my daughter's 16."},{"time":456000,"text":"He didn't want to come to Los Angeles."},{"time":458068,"text":"He loved it, but he had\na girlfriend in England."},{"time":461048,"text":"This was the love of his life, Sarah."},{"time":464761,"text":"He'd known her for a month."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467534,"text":"Mind you, they'd had\ntheir fourth anniversary,"},{"time":469814,"text":"because it's a long time when you're 16."},{"time":472777,"text":"He was really upset on the plane,"},{"time":474462,"text":"he said, \"I'll never find\nanother girl like Sarah.\""},{"time":476947,"text":"And we were rather pleased\nabout that, frankly --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479349,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":487395,"text":"Because she was the main reason\nwe were leaving the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490300,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":496059,"text":"But something strikes you\nwhen you move to America"},{"time":498425,"text":"and travel around the world:"},{"time":499815,"text":"Every education system on Earth\nhas the same hierarchy of subjects."},{"time":503537,"text":"Every one. Doesn't matter where you go."},{"time":505516,"text":"You'd think it would be\notherwise, but it isn't."},{"time":507810,"text":"At the top are mathematics and languages,"},{"time":509800,"text":"then the humanities,\nand at the bottom are the arts."},{"time":512258,"text":"Everywhere on Earth."},{"time":513400,"text":"And in pretty much every system too,\nthere's a hierarchy within the arts."},{"time":517519,"text":"Art and music are normally\ngiven a higher status in schools"},{"time":520400,"text":"than drama and dance."},{"time":521591,"text":"There isn't an education\nsystem on the planet"},{"time":523871,"text":"that teaches dance everyday to children"},{"time":525953,"text":"the way we teach them mathematics. Why?"},{"time":528524,"text":"Why not? I think this is rather important."},{"time":531249,"text":"I think math is very\nimportant, but so is dance."},{"time":533576,"text":"Children dance all the time\nif they're allowed to, we all do."},{"time":536500,"text":"We all have bodies, don't we?\nDid I miss a meeting?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542510,"text":"Truthfully, what happens is,\nas children grow up,"},{"time":544869,"text":"we start to educate them progressively\nfrom the waist up."},{"time":547661,"text":"And then we focus on their heads."},{"time":549310,"text":"And slightly to one side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551319,"text":"If you were to visit\neducation, as an alien,"},{"time":554000,"text":"and say \"What's it for, public education?\""},{"time":557000,"text":"I think you'd have to conclude,\nif you look at the output,"},{"time":559800,"text":"who really succeeds by this,"},{"time":561200,"text":"who does everything that they should,"},{"time":563000,"text":"who gets all the brownie\npoints, who are the winners --"},{"time":565755,"text":"I think you'd have to conclude\nthe whole purpose of public education"},{"time":569118,"text":"throughout the world"},{"time":570239,"text":"is to produce university professors."},{"time":572216,"text":"Isn't it?"},{"time":573551,"text":"They're the people who come out the top."},{"time":575558,"text":"And I used to be one, so there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577761,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580421,"text":"And I like university\nprofessors, but you know,"},{"time":583546,"text":"we shouldn't hold them up"},{"time":585045,"text":"as the high-water mark\nof all human achievement."},{"time":588000,"text":"They're just a form of life,"},{"time":590000,"text":"another form of life."},{"time":591584,"text":"But they're rather curious, and I say this\nout of affection for them."},{"time":594906,"text":"There's something curious\nabout professors in my experience --"},{"time":597900,"text":"not all of them, but typically,\nthey live in their heads."},{"time":600600,"text":"They live up there,\nand slightly to one side."},{"time":603495,"text":"They're disembodied, you know,\nin a kind of literal way."},{"time":606893,"text":"They look upon their body as a form\nof transport for their heads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610010,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616200,"text":"Don't they?"},{"time":617240,"text":"It's a way of getting\ntheir head to meetings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619486,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":625022,"text":"If you want real evidence\nof out-of-body experiences,"},{"time":628876,"text":"get yourself along to a residential\nconference of senior academics,"},{"time":632386,"text":"and pop into the discotheque\non the final night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634653,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637478,"text":"And there, you will see it."},{"time":638858,"text":"Grown men and women\nwrithing uncontrollably, off the beat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645891,"text":"Waiting until it ends so they can\ngo home and write a paper about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":651168,"text":"Our education system is predicated\non the idea of academic ability."},{"time":655035,"text":"And there's a reason."},{"time":656300,"text":"Around the world, there were\nno public systems of education,"},{"time":659880,"text":"really, before the 19th century."},{"time":662010,"text":"They all came into being\nto meet the needs of industrialism."},{"time":665269,"text":"So the hierarchy is rooted on two ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667456,"text":"Number one, that the most useful\nsubjects for work are at the top."},{"time":672077,"text":"So you were\nprobably steered benignly away"},{"time":674132,"text":"from things at school when you\nwere a kid, things you liked,"},{"time":677090,"text":"on the grounds that you would\nnever get a job doing that. Is that right?"},{"time":680500,"text":"Don't do music, you're not\ngoing to be a musician;"},{"time":682905,"text":"don't do art, you won't be an artist."},{"time":684730,"text":"Benign advice -- now, profoundly mistaken."},{"time":688174,"text":"The whole world\nis engulfed in a revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690343,"text":"And the second is academic ability,"},{"time":692464,"text":"which has really come to dominate\nour view of intelligence,"},{"time":695373,"text":"because the universities designed\nthe system in their image."},{"time":698300,"text":"If you think of it, the whole system\nof public education around the world"},{"time":701818,"text":"is a protracted process\nof university entrance."},{"time":704068,"text":"And the consequence\nis that many highly-talented,"},{"time":706425,"text":"brilliant, creative\npeople think they're not,"},{"time":708884,"text":"because the thing\nthey were good at at school"},{"time":711046,"text":"wasn't valued,\nor was actually stigmatized."},{"time":713383,"text":"And I think we can't afford\nto go on that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715703,"text":"In the next 30 years, according to UNESCO,"},{"time":718191,"text":"more people worldwide will be graduating"},{"time":721025,"text":"through education\nthan since the beginning of history."},{"time":723595,"text":"More people, and it's the combination\nof all the things we've talked about --"},{"time":727300,"text":"technology and its transformation\neffect on work, and demography"},{"time":730372,"text":"and the huge explosion in population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732200,"text":"Suddenly, degrees aren't worth anything."},{"time":735089,"text":"Isn't that true?"},{"time":736723,"text":"When I was a student,\nif you had a degree, you had a job."},{"time":739500,"text":"If you didn't have a job,\nit's because you didn't want one."},{"time":742300,"text":"And I didn't want one, frankly. (Laughter)"},{"time":745000,"text":"But now kids with degrees"},{"time":749098,"text":"are often heading home\nto carry on playing video games,"},{"time":752167,"text":"because you need an MA where\nthe previous job required a BA,"},{"time":755389,"text":"and now you need a PhD for the other."},{"time":757200,"text":"It's a process of academic inflation."},{"time":759000,"text":"And it indicates the whole\nstructure of education"},{"time":761400,"text":"is shifting beneath our feet."},{"time":762857,"text":"We need to radically rethink\nour view of intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765501,"text":"We know three things about intelligence."},{"time":767520,"text":"One, it's diverse."},{"time":768771,"text":"We think about the world in all the ways\nthat we experience it."},{"time":771800,"text":"We think visually, we think in sound,\nwe think kinesthetically."},{"time":774800,"text":"We think in abstract terms,\nwe think in movement."},{"time":777246,"text":"Secondly, intelligence is dynamic."},{"time":779587,"text":"If you look at the interactions\nof a human brain,"},{"time":782000,"text":"as we heard yesterday\nfrom a number of presentations,"},{"time":785000,"text":"intelligence is wonderfully interactive."},{"time":787000,"text":"The brain isn't divided into compartments."},{"time":789873,"text":"In fact, creativity --\nwhich I define as the process"},{"time":793000,"text":"of having original ideas\nthat have value --"},{"time":795349,"text":"more often than not comes about\nthrough the interaction"},{"time":798025,"text":"of different disciplinary\nways of seeing things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802310,"text":"By the way, there's a shaft of nerves\nthat joins the two halves of the brain"},{"time":806000,"text":"called the corpus callosum."},{"time":807515,"text":"It's thicker in women."},{"time":809088,"text":"Following off from Helen yesterday,"},{"time":810853,"text":"this is probably why women\nare better at multi-tasking."},{"time":814000,"text":"Because you are, aren't you?"},{"time":815841,"text":"There's a raft of research,\nbut I know it from my personal life."},{"time":819738,"text":"If my wife is cooking a meal at home --\nwhich is not often, thankfully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":827878,"text":"No, she's good at some things,\nbut if she's cooking,"},{"time":830400,"text":"she's dealing with people on the phone,"},{"time":832300,"text":"she's talking to the kids,\nshe's painting the ceiling,"},{"time":834880,"text":"she's doing open-heart surgery over here."},{"time":838000,"text":"If I'm cooking, the door\nis shut, the kids are out,"},{"time":841000,"text":"the phone's on the hook,\nif she comes in I get annoyed."},{"time":844000,"text":"I say, \"Terry, please,\nI'm trying to fry an egg in here.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":847095,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":854254,"text":"\"Give me a break.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":855478,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":857222,"text":"Actually, do you know\nthat old philosophical thing,"},{"time":859745,"text":"if a tree falls in a forest\nand nobody hears it, did it happen?"},{"time":863252,"text":"Remember that old chestnut?"},{"time":864605,"text":"I saw a great t-shirt\nrecently, which said,"},{"time":867038,"text":"\"If a man speaks his mind\nin a forest, and no woman hears him,"},{"time":871000,"text":"is he still wrong?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":872420,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":879976,"text":"And the third thing about intelligence is,"},{"time":882000,"text":"it's distinct."},{"time":883754,"text":"I'm doing a new book at the moment\ncalled \"Epiphany,\""},{"time":886351,"text":"which is based on a series\nof interviews with people"},{"time":888849,"text":"about how they discovered their talent."},{"time":890793,"text":"I'm fascinated\nby how people got to be there."},{"time":892986,"text":"It's really prompted by a conversation\nI had with a wonderful woman"},{"time":896200,"text":"who maybe most people\nhave never heard of, Gillian Lynne."},{"time":898900,"text":"Have you heard of her? Some have."},{"time":900554,"text":"She's a choreographer,\nand everybody knows her work."},{"time":903100,"text":"She did \"Cats\" and \"Phantom of the Opera.\""},{"time":905125,"text":"She's wonderful."},{"time":906127,"text":"I used to be on the board\nof The Royal Ballet,"},{"time":908297,"text":"as you can see."},{"time":909522,"text":"Anyway, Gillian and I had\nlunch one day and I said,"},{"time":912047,"text":"\"How did you get to be a dancer?\""},{"time":913976,"text":"It was interesting."},{"time":915000,"text":"When she was at school,\nshe was really hopeless."},{"time":917374,"text":"And the school, in the '30s,\nwrote to her parents and said,"},{"time":921000,"text":"\"We think Gillian\nhas a learning disorder.\""},{"time":923024,"text":"She couldn't concentrate;\nshe was fidgeting."},{"time":925190,"text":"I think now they'd say she had ADHD.\nWouldn't you?"},{"time":928504,"text":"But this was the 1930s, and ADHD\nhadn't been invented at this point."},{"time":932587,"text":"It wasn't an available condition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":935000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":937761,"text":"People weren't aware they could have that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939845,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":942003,"text":"Anyway, she went to see this specialist."},{"time":946305,"text":"So, this oak-paneled room,\nand she was there with her mother,"},{"time":950051,"text":"and she was led and sat\non this chair at the end,"},{"time":952552,"text":"and she sat on her hands for 20 minutes\nwhile this man talked to her mother"},{"time":956215,"text":"about the problems\nGillian was having at school."},{"time":958567,"text":"Because she was disturbing people;\nher homework was always late; and so on,"},{"time":962268,"text":"little kid of eight."},{"time":963388,"text":"In the end, the doctor\nwent and sat next to Gillian, and said,"},{"time":966467,"text":"\"I've listened to all these\nthings your mother's told me,"},{"time":969196,"text":"I need to speak to her privately."},{"time":970839,"text":"Wait here. We'll be back;\nwe won't be very long,\""},{"time":973239,"text":"and they went and left her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975588,"text":"But as they went out of the room,"},{"time":977248,"text":"he turned on the radio\nthat was sitting on his desk."},{"time":980342,"text":"And when they got out, he said to her\nmother, \"Just stand and watch her.\""},{"time":984000,"text":"And the minute they left the room,"},{"time":987015,"text":"she was on her feet, moving to the music."},{"time":989523,"text":"And they watched for a few minutes\nand he turned to her mother and said,"},{"time":993000,"text":"\"Mrs. Lynne, Gillian\nisn't sick; she's a dancer."},{"time":997000,"text":"Take her to a dance school.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":999000,"text":"I said, \"What happened?\""},{"time":1001000,"text":"She said, \"She did. I can't tell you\nhow wonderful it was."},{"time":1004000,"text":"We walked in this room\nand it was full of people like me."},{"time":1006777,"text":"People who couldn't sit still."},{"time":1009000,"text":"People who had to move to think.\"\nWho had to move to think."},{"time":1013746,"text":"They did ballet, they did tap, jazz;\nthey did modern; they did contemporary."},{"time":1017400,"text":"She was eventually auditioned\nfor the Royal Ballet School;"},{"time":1020244,"text":"she became a soloist; she had\na wonderful career at the Royal Ballet."},{"time":1023567,"text":"She eventually graduated\nfrom the Royal Ballet School,"},{"time":1026200,"text":"founded the Gillian Lynne Dance Company,"},{"time":1028200,"text":"met Andrew Lloyd Webber."},{"time":1029568,"text":"She's been responsible for"},{"time":1031001,"text":"some of the most successful\nmusical theater productions in history,"},{"time":1034172,"text":"she's given pleasure to millions,\nand she's a multi-millionaire."},{"time":1037269,"text":"Somebody else might have put her\non medication and told her to calm down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041364,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1048575,"text":"What I think it comes to is this:"},{"time":1050200,"text":"Al Gore spoke the other night"},{"time":1052000,"text":"about ecology and the revolution\nthat was triggered by Rachel Carson."},{"time":1057111,"text":"I believe our only hope for the future"},{"time":1059301,"text":"is to adopt a new conception\nof human ecology,"},{"time":1063158,"text":"one in which we start\nto reconstitute our conception"},{"time":1066000,"text":"of the richness of human capacity."},{"time":1068000,"text":"Our education system has mined our minds"},{"time":1071523,"text":"in the way that we strip-mine the earth:\nfor a particular commodity."},{"time":1075188,"text":"And for the future, it won't serve us."},{"time":1077696,"text":"We have to rethink\nthe fundamental principles"},{"time":1080000,"text":"on which we're educating our children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1082087,"text":"There was a wonderful quote\nby Jonas Salk, who said,"},{"time":1084785,"text":"\"If all the insects\nwere to disappear from the Earth,"},{"time":1089848,"text":"within 50 years all life\non Earth would end."},{"time":1093688,"text":"If all human beings\ndisappeared from the Earth,"},{"time":1096784,"text":"within 50 years all forms\nof life would flourish.\""},{"time":1100244,"text":"And he's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102291,"text":"What TED celebrates is the gift\nof the human imagination."},{"time":1106417,"text":"We have to be careful now"},{"time":1108512,"text":"that we use this gift wisely"},{"time":1110791,"text":"and that we avert some of the scenarios\nthat we've talked about."},{"time":1114044,"text":"And the only way we'll do it is by seeing\nour creative capacities"},{"time":1118000,"text":"for the richness they are"},{"time":1119634,"text":"and seeing our children\nfor the hope that they are."},{"time":1122840,"text":"And our task is to educate\ntheir whole being,"},{"time":1125262,"text":"so they can face this future."},{"time":1126770,"text":"By the way -- we may not see this future,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"but they will."},{"time":1130454,"text":"And our job is to help them\nmake something of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1133557,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134581,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}